Barclays, Lloyds, Rolls-Royce, JD: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-04-13T06:51:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/barclays-lloyds-rolls-royce-u-k-irish-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  Futures on the benchmark  FTSE 100 Index (UKX)  rose 0.5 percent to
5,956 at 7:51 a.m. in  London . The FTSE 100 yesterday declined
88.97, or 1.5 percent, to 5,964.47. The  FTSE All-Share Index (ASX) 
fell 1.4 percent, while Ireland’s ISEQ Index retreated 0.7
percent.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  : The London-based lender has sought
to discover for the last seven weeks how much it owes or is owed
for its purchase of Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc.’s brokerage, a
person familiar said. Barclays defeated Lehman’s bid to seize
$11 billion for the British bank’s alleged “windfall,”
following the acquisition. The stock fell 0.4 percent to 304.2
pence.  JD Sports Fashion Plc (JD/)  : The U.K.-based retailer
reported that full-year pretax profit increased 28 percent to
78.6 million pounds ($127.9 million) in the year ended Jan. 29.
The shares climbed 4.2 percent to 901.5 pence.  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  : The U.K. lender has
hired Lara Galliers to run its new central loan syndicate unit
in London, according to a person with knowledge of the matter.
The shares sank 3.3 percent to 60.3 pence.  Lonmin Plc (LMI)  : The world’s third-largest platinum
producer shut a shaft at its Marikana operation in  South Africa 
today following the company’s sixth fatal accident since Oct. 1.
The shares fell 3.2 percent to 1,688 pence.  Rolls-Royce Group Plc (RR/)  : Wyser-Pratte Management
Co., an investor in Tognum AG, rejected Daimler AG and Rolls-
Royce’s offer for the world’s second-largest engine maker as
“too low.” Rolls-Royce slid 1.6 percent to 619.5 pence.  Tullow Oil Plc (TLW)  : The company paid $469 million tied
to the purchase of Heritage Oil Plc’s interests in two oil
blocks, New Vision reported, citing Aston Kajara, the minister
of state for finance.  Separately, Tullow said it found gas condensate at its
Tweneboa-4 appraisal well off the coast of  Ghana . The company
also said it will resume drilling in the Lake Albert Rift basin
in Uganda in the next two weeks. The shares dropped 3.9 percent
to 1,413 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
